summary: An ordinance accepting a deed from A. T. Thomas and Lila A. Thomas, to the City of Seattle, dated March 28, 1910, to all that certain tract, lot or parcel of land, situate, lying and being in the County of King, State of Washington, particularly bounded and described as follows to-wit: North 33 feet of the north half of Northeast quarter of Northwest quarter of Southwest quarter of section 21, township 25 north, range 4 east, except portion condemned for sewer right of way by Ordinance No. 13265; to be used for an extension of East Lynn Street.
